Code Editors:-

A code editor is where developers write and manage code.
Editors are of two kinds:
IDEs (Integrated Development Environments)
Powerful, project-level tools with debugging, autocompletion, version control etc.

Popular IDEs:
Visual Studio Code (VS Code) – Free, cross-platform
WebStorm – Paid, powerful
Visual Studio Community (Windows) – Good for .NET + JS

Lightweight Editors
Fast, simple editors mainly used for single files.

Examples:
Sublime Text
Notepad++
Vim / Emacs
IDE = Project-level powerful tool
Lightweight = Quick file editing
Choose based on project and personal preference.
